  "title": "Safety Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>Assist in the implementation of the Safety Management System on the worksite. Daily conduct site safety inspection and take appropriate corrective actions. Prepares necessary reports (Inspection, Incident/accident report &amp; etc). Conduct in-house safety training. Conduct safety briefing. Inspect the workplace to ensure safety measure are being implemented and maintained. Conduct risk assessment and identify safety hazards on site to ensure safety compliance are met</p>\n<p>Minimum 2 years’ of relevant working experience in Building construction</p>\n<p>Possess relevant Certificates (e.g. Advanced Certificate in WSH Safety Coordinators Training Course)</p>\n<p>Certification in Lifting Supervisors Safety Course</p>\n<p>Certification in MWAH</p>\n<p>Certification in Supervision of Metal Scaffold Erection Course (Optional)</p>\n<p>Occupational First Aid Course (OFA) (Optional)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=2ahUKEwi2o5ml2cfvAhWJWisKHcylDMcQFjAAegQIAhAD&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fcourses.ntuclearninghub.com%2Fbrowse%2Fworkplace-safety-and-health%2Fprograms%2Fassess-confined-space-for-safe-entry-and-work&amp;usg=AOvVaw2G3qY6ihlH1wXdNimsCYdq\">Assess Confined Space For Safe Entry And Work</a> (Optional)</p>",
